Frequently Asked Questions About Nationals Park Events and Tickets

What events are at Nationals Park?

Nationals Park is primarily used as the home of MLB's Washington Nationals. However, Nationals Park does host a number of concerts and other events. See full Nationals Park schedule above.

How much are tickets at Nationals Park?

Nationals Park ticket prices on the secondary market can vary depending on a number of factors. Typically, Nationals Park tickets can be found for as low as $13.00, with an average price of $53.00 but can vary depending on the event.

What is Nationals Park's address?

Nationals Park is located at 1500 S Capitol St SE, Washington, DC 20003

What city is Nationals Park in?

Nationals Park is located in Washington

What is the capacity of Nationals Park?

Nationals Park has a capacity of roughly 41339, though it will depend somewhat on the event type.

When was Nationals Park opened?

Nationals Park was opened in 2008

Can you purchase tickets at the Nationals Park box office?

Yes, you can purchase tickets at the box office. Please visit the official box office site for more details.

What is the phone number for Nationals Park?

Nationals Park's phone number is 202-675-6287

Does Nationals Park offer concessions for sale?

Yes, you can purchase concessions at Nationals Park. Please visit the official site for more details.

Does Nationals Park have a coat check?

Yes, Nationals Park has a coat check.

Where can I find details on will call?

You can find details about will call on the Nationals Park's official site.

When do gates open?

It depends on the event but gates at Nationals Park will typically open 2 hour(s) before the event.

Are bags allowed at Nationals Park?

Yes, bags are allowed at Nationals Park, but there are exceptions and we strongly recommend visiting the official Nationals Park site for the latest details.

Are laptops allowed at Nationals Park?

Yes, laptops are allowed at Nationals Park, but we recommend visiting the official Nationals Park site for the latest details.

Are cameras allowed at Nationals Park?

Cameras are allowed at Nationals Park but professional cameras are not permitted, please visit the venue's oficial site for full details on their camera policy.

Can I bring outside food to Nationals Park?

Yes, you can bring outside food to Nationals Park, but we recommend visiting the venue's official site for more details.

Are outside drinks allowed at Nationals Park?

Yes, outside drinks are allowed at Nationals Park, but we recommend visiting the venue's official site for more details.

Are animals allowed at Nationals Park?

Only service animals are allowed at Nationals Park

At what age do you need a ticket to enter Nationals Park?

Nationals Park requires a ticket for any child who is 3 or above. Please visit the official site for more details.

What is the phone number for disabled services at Nationals Park?

888-632-6287
